replies.bodyText:
mmh with the REQUESTED_FROM_SOURCE guard, but we indeed don't really use that to ensure n is correct here.
let's unpack that a little:

addCap should lose to compareAndSet (other writes "happens before")
since parallel requests are illegal, the only way addCap loses is if compareAndSet switched from 0 to 1, so at that point requestedFromSource == 0 or 1
it should thus be safe to use the return value of addCap (0 or 1) as a modifier to n for the parent request:

long delta = Operators.addCap(REQUESTED_FROM_SOURCE, this, n);
s.request(n - delta);
